
[1]boon

   BOON, n. [L. bonus.]

   1. A gift; a grant; a benefaction; a present; a favor granted.

   2. A prayer, or petition.

   BOON, a. [L. bonus.] Gay; merry; kind; bountiful; as a boon companion.
